CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 23, 1960, p. 2, reads: "Jaycees Honor Jamal - The Pittsburgh Junior Chamber of Commerce honored Ahmad Jamal, center, a native son, as top man in entertainment field at its annual awards banquet at the Hotel Penn - Sheraton Monday night.  Flanking the outstanding jazz pianist are Herbert May, left, civic service awardee, and Stanley Pernel, human relations winer [winner]. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Herbert May, Ahmad Jamal holding plaque presented by The Pittsburgh Junior Chamber of Commerce, and Stanley Pernel, standing in Penn Sheraton Hotel, horizontal format
